{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17610473","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17610473"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:02:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:02:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16176"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16176","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16176"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.71,0.05,0.03,0,0.21]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8867"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115218"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8867","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8867"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16176"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97226"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"7017"},{"type":"tags","id":"10644"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21117"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21119"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115218","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/115218"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe breast contains specialised glandular tissue organised into functional units.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the terminal duct lobular unit of the breast?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["A cluster of acini draining into terminal ducts","A collection of adipose tissue supporting the ductal system","A network of lymphatic vessels surrounding milk ducts","A single milk-producing cell that secretes into a duct","A group of myoepithelial cells that contract to express milk"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecluster of acini draining into terminal ducts\u003C/strong\u003E correctly describes the terminal duct lobular unit (TDLU). Each TDLU consists of multiple small, spherical acini (also called alveoli) that connect to terminal ducts. These structures are the basic functional units of the breast where milk production occurs during lactation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA single milk-producing cell that secretes into a duct\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as the TDLU is a complex structure containing many cells, not just a single cell. \u003Cstrong\u003EA network of lymphatic vessels surrounding milk ducts\u003C/strong\u003E does not describe the TDLU since while lymphatics are present in breast tissue, they are not part of the TDLU. \u003Cstrong\u003EA group of myoepithelial cells that contract to express milk\u003C/strong\u003E represents only one component of the TDLU rather than the complete structure. \u003Cstrong\u003EA collection of adipose tissue supporting the ductal system\u003C/strong\u003E refers to supportive tissue that provides structural support but is not part of the TDLU itself.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe TDLU is clinically significant as it is the site of origin for most breast cancers, particularly ductal and lobular carcinomas.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The terminal duct lobular unit (TDLU) is the functional unit of the breast consisting of multiple acini (alveoli) that drain into terminal ducts.","Terminal duct lobular units are the site of milk production during lactation and the origin of most breast cancers."],"references":["Zucca-Matthes G, Urban C, Vallejo A. Anatomy of the nipple and breast ducts. Gland Surg. 2016 Feb;5(1):32-6. doi: 10.3978/j.issn.2227-684X.2015.05.10. PMID: 26855906; PMCID: PMC4716863","Javed A, Lteif A. Development of the human breast. Semin Plast Surg. 2013 Feb;27(1):5-12. doi: 10.1055/s-0033-1343989. PMID: 24872732; PMCID: PMC3706056","Biswas SK, Banerjee S, Baker GW, Kuo CY, Chowdhury I. The Mammary Gland: Basic Structure and Molecular Signaling during Development. Int J Mol Sci. 2022 Mar 31;23(7):3883. doi: 10.3390/ijms23073883. PMID: 35409243; PMCID: PMC8998991","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97226"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16176"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97226","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/97226"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-23T10:08:05+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-23T10:10:45+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8867"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115218"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","